The Nigerian Meteorological Agency (NiMet) has predicted thundery, rainy activities across the country for Wednesday. NiMet’s weather outlook on Tuesday in Abuja predicted thunderstorms over Kano and Katsina of the Northern States in the morning hours. It predicted thunderstorm over Kano, Katsina, Potiskum, Damaturu, Dutse and Gusau later in the day with day and night temperatures of 30 to 34 degree Celsius and 23 to 26 degree Celsius respectively. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE ” For Central States, partly cloudy to cloudy condition is anticipated over the region in the morning hours. ” There are prospects of thunderstorms over Jos, Gombe, Yola, Mambila Plateau and Bauchi during the afternoon/evening hours. “Day and night temperature values are expected to be 28 to 34 degree Celsius and 18 to 24 degree Celsius respectively, ” NiMet said . According to it, cloudy conditions are expected over the Southern States with chances of rain over Warri, Benin and Asaba axis in the morning. The agency predicted intermittent rains over most places in the region later in the day with day and night temperatures of 29 to 32 degree Celsius and 21 to 24 degree Celsius respectively. Thursday: NiMET makes weather prediction for Abuja, Kano, Lagos, others NiMET predicts clouds, thunder for Saturday NiMET predicts rains, thunderstorms for Sunday Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin